'SOUTH CENTRAL' OFFENSIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What I can't believe is that a quality show like "Thea" (ABC), which 
exemplifies a positive black family that everyone can enjoy, is yanked off the 
air for "Home Improvement" reruns and an idiotic, stereotypical "South Central" 
(Fox) appears to further humiliate African Americans. The language is crude and 
the jokes are trite and it offends me as a South Central Angeleno. 
</P>
<P>
 Dion A. Richardson, Los Angeles 
