<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONNIE JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *** Chris Walker, "Sincerely Yours," Pendulum/ERG. At first listening, Walker 
hardly seems distinguishable from other soulful balladeers of the Peabo Bryson/ 
James Ingram variety.It's as a songwriter that Walker shines, be it on the 
frisky invitation of "Do Me" -- or "Love Tonight," on which he extends his 
attention to a single mom who's more concerned with unpaid bills than a casual 
fling. At last, a responsible love-man for the '90s. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent). CONNIE JOHNSON 
</P>
