<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECORD RACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHERINE TURMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ** Carcass, "Heartwork," Earache/Columbia. Has British grindcore band Carcass 
matured since its early death-metal songs such as "Feast on Dismembered 
Carnage"? The hyper-speed riffs and depths-of-hell vocals on "Heartwork" say 
no.But Carcass' fourth record in nine years does take a slightly more melodic 
and accessible approach, though the lyrics are still as deliberately abstruse 
as the band's dense musicality.  
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent). KATHERINE TURMAN 
</P>
