<P>
 *** The Young Dubliners, "Rocky Road," Scotti Bros. Strong pop songwriting and 
a touch of the traditional Irish music that rouses them at the band's home pub, 
Santa Monica's Fair City, mark this brisk, six-song major-label debut.The 
dexterous instrumental "Ashley Falls" and Merseybeat descendant "Last House on 
the Street" highlight a promising beginning. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent). BRUCE HARING 
