By RANDY LEWIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *** Mike Henderson, "Country Music Made Me Do It," BMG. Henderson's debut is 
refreshingly devoid of country cliches.A popular studio guitarist, Henderson 
shows his skills here as a producer, singer and, especially, writer, finding 
hard truth beneath the surface wit of "Fountain of Youth" and tapping classic 
honky-tonk wish fulfillment in "If the Jukebox Took Teardrops." 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent). RANDY LEWIS 
