<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Katherine Turman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 VOCAL BREAK: Jeff Charroux, lead singer of the band Ultra Violet Eye, is 
sitting in for Greta's Paul Plagens on Greta's current East Coast tour while 
Plagens completes his recovery program at a Los Angeles-area substance abuse 
rehabilitation center. 
</P>
<P>
 "We assumed the band wouldn't be able to do the tour," says Mercury Records' 
Mike Sikkas, East Coast senior director of A&R."On a creative level, it didn't 
really fly . . . but after considerable discussion -- and Paul was in the loop 
on all of this -- rather than disrupt the momentum and have the whole band 
victimized, we chose to continue with the tour." 
</P>
<P>
 Plagens hopes to rejoin Greta, which created such a buzz on the Los Angeles 
rock scene in 1992 that it became the object of a major record company bidding 
war, for scheduled dates with Motorhead beginning next Sunday. Katherine Turman 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
