<HEADLINE>
<P>
VIDAL ORGANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In last Sunday's "Little Box in the Lower Left-Hand Corner," Pam Palmer cites 
a recent Film Clip, asking what the big deal is concerning male frontal nudity. 
</P>
<P>
 Gore Vidal has elucidated this point in one of his essays ("Women's 
Liberation: Feminism and Its Discontents"): "Though female nudes have been 
usually accepted in our Puritan culture, until recently the male nude was 
unacceptable to the Patriarchs. After all, the male -- any male -- is a 
stand-in for God, and God wears a suit at all times, or at least jockey 
shorts." 
</P>
<P>
 RICK SANDFORD 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
