<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; CHARITY: NEW CHIEF FOR BIG BROTHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brentwood resident Bob Waldorf has been named president of Jewish Big Brothers 
of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Waldorf had a Big Brother when he was a child and went on to be a mentor in 
the program when he was older. He has served on the board of directors for 
Jewish Big Brothers for more than two decades. He is owner and president of 
Idea Man Inc., a promotional products business in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Jewish Big Brothers of Los Angeles is a nonprofit agency providing a range of 
programs for children ages 7 to 12, most of whom are from single-parent homes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
