COMMUNITY NEWS: HANCOCK PARK; CLUB SETTLES LAWSUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Wilshire Country Club and a black employee who had worked in the kitchen 
for 15 years have settled a lawsuit in which the woman accused her boss of 
racial and sexual harassment and discrimination, her attorney said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dan Stormer, the attorney for Margaret Inyama, said he could not reveal the 
terms of the settlement, but did say that Inyama was pleased with the outcome. 
</P>
<P>
 Club officials denied the allegations when she filed her lawsuit last year. 
</P>
