<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN WITH FOREHEAD TATTOOS COMPENSATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A court blamed India's most feared state police force for an attack that left 
four women with the word "pickpocket" tattooed across their foreheads. 
</P>
<P>
 In a ruling Thursday, Judges A. P. Choudhury and J. L. Gupta ordered the 
Punjab state government to pay the women the equivalent of $1,600 each and to 
file a report detailing how much more money they needed for damages. 
</P>
