<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW PITCHES FOR USE OF EL TORO MCAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Here's an idea to solve some of Orange County's most pressing problems at 
once. Use the El Toro Air Base to build a new state-of-the-art ballpark for the 
Angels a la Baltimore's successful Camden Yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The setting would be beautiful with the Saddleback Mountains towering over the 
outfield. Pay for it with a countywide tax on alcohol and cigarettes. It has 
been done elsewhere. 
</P>
<P>
 Then Anaheim could refurbish the "Big A" to keep the Rams and make it a better 
stadium for football fans. Just the construction alone on these projects would 
pump up the economy for North and South County alike. 
</P>
<P>
 SALLY GOLD 
</P>
<P>
 Lake Forest 
</P>
<P>
 * Re: The final solution for the El Toro Marine Corps Air Station: As the 
countless suggestions and ideas are being considered, there is one very 
predictable course of action, some might eventually say a course of no action. 
</P>
<P>
 Immediately designate the Irvine City Council as the supreme administrator 
over El Toro MCAS. The City Council will immediately hold countless meetings, 
while putting various city departments in charge to coordinate all the 
activities at all the meetings. 
</P>
<P>
 Along the way the council will vote for many options and at subsequent 
meetings will vote to change the votes at the previously held meetings. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council and city bureaucrats "own the process," so whatever citizens' 
suggestions are put forth will be overruled by a city-hired outside 
guru-expert, who will only attend the one meeting that he conducts. The outside 
guru-expert will then put forth a consensus by having citizens do pencil 
drawings and finger paintings while searching for the best possible plan. The 
so called consensus is actually the dictate of the outside guru-expert. 
</P>
<P>
 The reason this is such an excellent plan: While all the countless meetings 
are being held, absolutely nothing will happen. The El Toro MCAS will just lie 
fallow and rot, with no jails, no airport, no housing development. 
</P>
<P>
 The very best part is that all the meeting activity will only take at least 10 
years to provide no decisions and hence absolutely no problems! This time 
projection is verified by the City Council's and city bureaucrats' previous and 
present track record. 
</P>
<P>
 The citizens of Northwood, especially the ones living along the abandoned 
railroad right-of-way, will be most pleased to let you know what 10 years of 
City Council meetings have provided for Northwood. Namely a number of 
frustrated citizens who some day might get off their couches and get rid of 
Irvine's incumbent politicians like Tustin did in their last election. 
</P>
<P>
 FRANK J. RUNZLER 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 
</P>
