<HEADLINE>
<P>
DON'T CATER TO LAST-MINUTE TAX FILERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Re "Tax Time Tribulations," April 15: I see that the U.S. post offices in 
both Orange and Los Angeles counties provided special service for those filing 
last-minute tax returns by remaining open in some cases until midnight. 
</P>
<P>
 As a responsible citizen, I find this unfair to the millions of other 
law-abiding and punctual citizens of this area. 
</P>
<P>
 With the price of postage on a steady rise, and the cost in overtime pay and 
other operating budget expenses, I feel that it is unfair to the majority of 
taxpayers to support those persons who are either too negligent or too selfish 
in filing their returns (at the last minute). This is just another I reason why 
the cost of public services is constantly on the upswing. 
</P>
<P>
 BILL SMITH 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo 
</P>
</TEXT>
