<P>
LAGUNA EVENT A WALK ON THE MILD SIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * April 9 was one of the most rewarding Saturdays we have spent in a long, 
long time. 
</P>
<P>
 We were fortunate enough to participate in the Sawdust Festival ArtWalk for 
the first time.We understand that this is the third annual event. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sawdust Festival ArtWalk has to be the best-kept secret in Laguna Beach. 
We visited the studios/homes of seven artists. 
</P>
<P>
 Those of us who live in Laguna and appreciate the beauty our artist friends 
and neighbors create must take personally the responsibility to maintain the 
quality of the life we all enjoy and our artists thrive on. 
</P>
<P>
 This delightful event is what Laguna is all about. 
</P>
<P>
 There is so much anguish, pain and negativism in our world. It was a welcome 
change to be able to truly and deeply enjoy what is meaningful about our 
special community. 
</P>
<P>
 K.A. TURNER 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 
