<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOCCER / SENIOR BOYS' ALL-STAR GAME; NORTH HOLDS OFF SOUTH, SCORES IN 
SECOND HALF FOR 3-0 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a scoreless first half, the North team finally broke through to score 
three second-half goals and defeated the South, 3-0, in the Orange County Boys' 
Soccer Coaches Assn. all-star game Saturday at Chapman University. 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim goalkeeper Joel Vasquez put a noose around the South's potent scoring 
attack, and the North fullbacks, led by Ken Cody and Oscar Lara and a stingy 
defense, stepped in at crucial times to smother each South rally. 
</P>
<P>
 By halftime, it appeared as if neither team would be able to break through as 
South goalkeeper Pete Van de Ven knocked away each North scoring chance. 
</P>
<P>
 But it was the Sunny Hills duo of Doug Howes and D.J. Buckley that put the 
North on the scoreboard six minutes into the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Howes, who was notified on Tuesday that he would be filling in for teammate 
Chris Roselli, took a pass down the right side until he spotted Buckley 
charging toward the left post. Howes fed his Lancer teammate perfectly and 
Buckley redirected the ball past Van de Ven. 
</P>
<P>
 After the South's two scoring chances hit the crossbar, the North cushioned 
its lead with 12 minutes left when Van de Ven and fullback Oscar Cisneros 
misplayed a long indirect kick from Cody. 
</P>
<P>
 Both players called for the ball at the same time, but then stopped and looked 
at each other. Meanwhile, Orange forward Hugo Regalado raced in, knocked the 
ball away from both players and fired into the open net for a 2-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The South made it 3-0 with under three minutes to play on a goal from Santa 
Ana Valley's Rafael Reynosa on an assist from Buckley. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were fortunate to win this game," North Coach Fred Leininger said. "Both 
teams played superb, but our shots found the back of the net." 
</P>
</TEXT>
