<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUSTICE DEPARTMENT JOINS CASE AGAINST MEDICAL SUPPLIER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Justice Department has taken over a lawsuit by two whistle blowers 
charging a national distributor of medical equipment with overbilling Medicare. 
</P>
<P>
 The suit was brought against Curative Technologies Inc. and its former 
subsidiary, UltraMed Inc. of Avoca, Pa., for allegedly fraudulent billing of 
lymphedema pumps to Medicare, the federal old-age health insurance program, 
Assistant Atty. Gen. Frank Hunger said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The pumps are used to treat severe circulatory conditions. 
</P>
