<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; CITY TO CONSIDER COUNTYWIDE BUS PASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley bus riders will be able to travel farther for the same amount of 
money if the City Council approves the use of a countywide pass at Monday's 
meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 The passes would be good on Simi Valley buses, intercity buses and those in 
other cities that approve the plan.Several cities are considering approving the 
$34 monthly passes. 
</P>
<P>
 "The ease with which you can ride with a single pass and the new intercity 
service will likely increase ridership," said Judy Collins, deputy director of 
Community Services for Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Collins said the Ventura County Transportation Commission plans to sell the 
new passes this summer when it starts its new intercity bus service. Money from 
the passes will be divided based on the number of riders within each city, she 
said. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
