<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; MARKET OWNER ROBBED, TIED UP BY GUNMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The owner of a neighborhood market in Santa Paula was confronted by an armed 
man, robbed and tied up after she opened her store Saturday morning, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man apparently broke into Gil's Market at 1220 Saticoy St. and waited for 
the owner to open her business just before 9 a.m., Santa Paula police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The owner, whose name was not released, was forced to open the safe and hand 
over an undisclosed amount of cash to the gunman, a police spokesman said. 
After robbing the woman, the gunman tied her up and then fled. She was able to 
escape soon after and was unharmed, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 No description of the suspect was provided by police, who said the robbery is 
under investigation. SCOTT HADLY 
