<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: HAZARDOUS-WASTE DISPOSER SUED BY FORMER LANDLORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Security Environmental Systems Inc., a hazardous-waste disposer, said Friday 
that it is being sued by the owner of a Vernon warehouse. The company had once 
hoped to convert the site into a hazardous-waste incinerator. 
</P>
<P>
 Under intense community pressure, Security Environmental abandoned plans 
several years ago to build the medical-waste burner at the Los Angeles County 
site. The property owner alleges in its suit that Security Environmental owes 
back rent and did not clean up the site, the company said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
 Security Environmental President Ellen Batzel defended the company, saying 
that its engineers have left the facility pristine and that city officials are 
expected to issue a report confirming that. 
</P>
<P>
 The company did not comment on the allegations that it owes back rent. 
</P>
<P>
 Security Environmental also said that it is being sued for allegedly breaking 
an oral agreement to pay 250,000 shares of its common stock for services 
allegedly rendered to the company in 1990. 
</P>
