HISTORY LESSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Your attempt to remake history ("Events," April 17) should be pointed out. In 
May, 1864, Gen. William Tecumseh Sherman was nowhere near Virginia. He was just 
beginning his famous march to Atlanta -- starting from Chattanooga, Tenn. Gen. 
Ulysses S. Grant was in command of the Federal troops at the Wilderness. 
</P>
