<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARNOLD GARCIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The Probation Commission wishes to thank The Times for the accurate account 
of the tragedy that took place at the Probation Department's Dorothy Kirby 
Treatment Center. Your report of the brutal attack upon and subsequent death of 
Arnold Garcia, a group supervisor, was handled with considerable restraint and 
sensitivity (April 6, 10). 
</P>
<P>
 In the weeks ahead, a major effort will be spent in determining how and why 
the sad event took place, and the steps that can be taken to avoid subsequent 
acts of violence by young people involved with the juvenile justice system. 
Unfortunately, though necessary, these fact-finding efforts will in no way 
comfort Arnold Garcia's widow and 11 children, one of whom is only 10 months 
old. 
</P>
<P>
 It is the Probation Commission's hope that your readers translate their shock 
and sympathy into actions that will benefit the family of a man who spent 17 
years of his life worrying about other people's children. Perhaps we can repay 
the debt and help his family with a contribution to the Arnold Garcia Memorial 
Fund, c/o Paul Higa, Probation Department Headquarters, 9150 E. Imperial 
Highway, Room N-91, Downey, 90242. 
</P>
<P>
 BETTY ROSENSTEIN 
</P>
<P>
 President, Probation Commission 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles County 
</P>
