<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: WATTS; POST OFFICE PUTS WATTS ON ITS MAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. Postal Service has officially designated Watts a mailing address for 
certain ZIP codes. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents in the 90002, 90059, 90061 and 90044 ZIP codes can now write Watts 
as a return address. 
</P>
<P>
 The move by the Postal Service follows a request from City Councilman Rudy 
Svorinich, who represents the 15th Council District. 
</P>
<P>
 Svorinich made the request in January, urging Postmaster General Marvin Runyon 
to recognize the area because it would "acknowledge the pride, hard work and 
respect it truly deserves." 
</P>
