<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEADLINE FOR QUAKE AID EXTENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The nonprofit Community Financial Resource Center, a project of the Los 
Angeles Community Reinvestment Committee, is offering free assistance to 
South-Central property and business owners who suffered damage and losses in 
the Jan. 17 earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline for applying for earthquake assistance at the center, 4060 S. 
Figueroa St., has been extended to May 17. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers from commercial banks assist applicants with packaging and 
submitting applications, obtaining information on lending programs, acquiring 
technical assistance and identifying potential rebuilding contractors. 
</P>
<P>
 Services are available to businesses and residents in an area bounded by Pico 
Boulevard to the north, Alameda Street to the east, San Pedro to the south and 
Venice Beach to the west. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 233-1900. 
</P>
