<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * If you have a warm, sunny corner in your garden that's bare, consider 
planting a gardenia shrub or two. Their lovely, fragrant white flowers add 
their scent to the garden and indoors when cut to fill vases. 
</P>
<P>
 * Mulching in flower beds around shrubs and annuals and in the vegetable 
garden will help conserve soil moisture and reduce the weeds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
