<P>
 An article April 3 on art appreciation in the digital age confused the market 
availability of some products developed at the Art Institute of Chicago.An 
interactive computer game inviting children to go on a pre-Columbian treasure 
hunt or deconstruct a Louise Nevelson sculpture is for use at the museum only 
and has not been marketed. A children's laser disc, "With Open Eyes," is sold 
by Voyager. An interactive program on ancient art is being developed in-house 
at the museum and is expected to be completed in late 1995. 
</P>
